<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n49002d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n49" href="#n49002d">N49 (VI.B.39)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n49all.htm#n49002d"> 2(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> sweetman</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Rowan thus tells how he got away from Ireland:&mdash; &ldquo;But in my acknowledgments how am I to mention the generous, disinterested conduct of the two brothers Sheridan, farmers and boatmen, of Baldoyle, who upon being introduced to me by Mr. <mark>Sweetman</mark>, of Howth, and in possession of the proclamation offering &pound;3,000 for my capture, and knowing me only by name, not only concealed me while sheltering at Mr. Sweetman&apos;s house, but consented to carry me in their small half-decked fishing boat across the Channel to the coast of France, saying to Mr. Sweetman, &lsquo;Never fear; by &mdash;, we&apos;ll land him safe. And so they did, in two days, although driven back once from near Wexford to take shelter under Howth.&rdquo; <small> James Collins, <a name="JCLO2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JCLO2"><cite title="source">Life in Old Dublin</cite></a> (l913) 34</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
